Author: karsa <wanghongtao114@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 2 16:28:22 2026 +0800

    fix: close overlays on tab switch and prevent More/Settings z-index conflict
    
    When a tab was switched while Settings was open, the overlay remained
    on screen blocking the new tab content. Also, opening the More drawer
    while Settings was open placed the drawer under the Settings backdrop
    (z-idx 98 vs 300), making it unreachable.
    
    Fix: auto-close Settings and More when active tab changes, and add
    mutual-exclusion in the More button onClick handler.
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>

